			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I hope that title hasn't caused 1000 monitors to be bashed out of frustration. Yes, I'm looking for any help or advice to get inside the elusive resourcedatabase.dat, track down the reference to the particular texture that I'm looking for, then change the value so that it points to another texture of choice. I do not need to know how to insert my own textures. I hope that makes the job a little easier.
<br />

<br />
  I've been reading through similar topics on this forum but have not got anywhere with them yet. I gather that I have to use aodbtool, know how to unparse, be familiar with C-Tree (dont know why yet), use Edhex, replace a blob (?) after the texture argument ect ect. I have all those programs and am hacking away at the problem patiently but still no success. More experienced members are probably already gathering that I'm completely lost ;) What I really need is some kind person to give me a specific example. Then it will all make sense.
<br />

<br />
   So.. for example... How would I swap the textures of Inferior Kevlar Armor vest (8729) so that it looks like Blue Fancy Shirt (42249) ? Please, if you can, go through step by step and tell me what values to change in Resourcedatabase.dat, how you attained those values, and what programs are needed to achieve this? I hope its fairly simple.. 
<br />

<br />
   I have some basic programming skills and have already successfully skinned many other games. But for some reason I'm finding AO incredibly difficult! Please dont laugh! I've been playing AO for a few months now and am disappointed with how my avatar looks. Sometimes a few novelties (like removing that ugly rusty armor and donning a james bond suit while keeping the same AP) can breathe life back in to the game and get me interested again. Aware that changes are only visible to client side. Also aware of the nude patch, have it, and while it was good for a 2 minute chuckle, this doesnt help my MALE avatar look cool! 
<br />

<br />
   Appreciate any advice you can give. Thankyou!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
