			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Im at work and may be wrong with my assumption of this as the resourcedb is the least of my projects worries at the moment.
<br />
I know on other files tho AO does a CRC check on each main game file further protected by an md5 sig(again not sure if the db is included). If it is it means any modifications will cause the game to repatch. An easy way to get around that would be a simple memory patch to jump the crc check in the main exe.  But thats a dirty way of doing it.
<br />

<br />
An easy (specially if they are the same length numbers) but messy way as you seem to be suggesting would be to just hex the aoids, of course swapping them can have detrimental effects, for example... the client does some low level cheking on items, that is it checks first before it even attempts for the server to verify. So if you say swap azure with like a med suits aoid, you not only lose the treatment buff but the game wont let you equip it because its referencing all the stats of azure, including level and reqs...   And when you try to put on an implant or whatever the client will send some invalid stats and the server will prolly set off somy kind of exploiter alarm bells =)
<br />

<br />
Another way would be to change the MESH ids, naturally you would need to change each mesh and a simple hex edit will allow that no sweat.
<br />
You could start with somethign easy... changing the colour of AB tank to HNT.  As both ids are the same lenth  you could switch it in a jiffy.
<br />

<br />
Again this is all hard modding and it would be alot better to go around via a memory patch to intercept certain mesh calls. Its cleaner, neater and doesnt screw with the client.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
