			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I dont know. The texture swap works, though.. Wearing battered nomad armor can now look like Miiir items or even a wicked tattoo. Havent changed anything major. Only the reference to which texture is displayed on my client, not the actual item in hand. I dont think i messed with the AOID... 
<br />

<br />
  Anyway its a bit of fun seeing what I can create. Also checking out some textures on items that I will probably never possess. wow they look so cool : )
<br />

<br />
  A few days and still no patch or nasty visits from GM's. In my modest experience with skinning/modding its relatively harmless and undetectable by server. Usually the only problem you get is whenever the client needs a major update and then everything is reset. Many MPORG's/MPOG's turn a blind eye to the practice or even allow it. From what I hear, the GM's arent majorly fussed with altering skins. The only cases I have heard of which resulted in a ban is some guy trying to hack the actual properties of his inventory (increase its stat's/effects or hack to a higher level item) and some other guy flounting pictures of nude avatars on the AO forum (real smart!).
<br />

<br />
   So... not to start a debate on AOID's or anything.. If anybody is interested in this send a pm</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
