			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The AOID is the thing.
<br />
Meshes are nothing, simply a reference to the textures in the DB.
<br />
The AOID is a reference of the actual item attributes, if you change the AOID on a buff item you will get a visit im sure.  Its stupid to do that anyway cause the server will reject it, not to mention it will make doing things a little confusing liek trying to put an imp in and wonderign why the server rejects you even tho it looks like you have the stats to wear it. For instance imagine makign a medsuit have the id of azure BP nto onyl can u not equip the medsuit anymore but to actuall get the treatment benefit you would have to drop peter lee or something <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
I do think FC care about skining as it does involve a certain level of reverse engineering. Whilst i cant see any real benefit of changing skins because no 1 else can see it I can actually see some ways to exploit it... So I wouldnt go around saying its safe and promoting it. We really dont know FC's stance... but if all your doing is modding player textures no real harm.
<br />
If all you do is change meshes theres no harm and its not detectable... unless FC go nuts and include periodic crc/md5 db checks server side, then they will spot you from a mile away (But I dont think thats going to  happen =) ).
<br />

<br />

<br />
Neph</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
